.TH DICTEE 1 "February 2025" "dictee 0.3.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dictee \- push-to-talk voice dictation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dictee
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dictee
is a push-to-talk dictation script designed to be bound to a keyboard shortcut.
.PP
.B First call:
starts recording from microphone and displays animation.
.PP
.B Second call:
stops recording, transcribes via transcribe-daemon, and types the result
using ydotool.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.TP
.B transcribe-daemon
Must be running (via systemd or manually)
.TP
.B ydotool
For typing the transcribed text
.TP
.B pw-record
For audio recording (PipeWire)
.SH ANIMATION
The script supports an optional visual animation during recording.
Configure in /usr/bin/dictee:
.PP
.RS
BIN_PATH="/path/to/animation-speech"
.br
ANIMATION_CONFIG="circular"
.br
ANIMATION_PARAM="-p center -w 1000 -H 150"
.RE
.PP
The animation receives SIGUSR1 to start and SIGUSR2 to stop.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /tmp/dictee.pid
PID of pw-record process
.TP
.I /tmp/dictee_anim.pid
PID of animation process
.TP
.I /tmp/dictee_recording.wav
Temporary recording file
.SH SETUP
.PP
1. Enable the transcription daemon:
.RS
systemctl --user enable --now dictee
.RE
.PP
2. Enable ydotool daemon:
.RS
systemctl --user enable --now ydotool
.RE
.PP
3. Bind /usr/bin/dictee to a keyboard shortcut in your desktop environment.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR transcribe-daemon (1),
.BR transcribe-client (1),
.BR ydotool (1)
.SH AUTHOR
rcspam <rcspams@gmail.com>
